    <div id="Races" class="w3-container menu w3-padding-48 w3-card">
      <p class="w3-text-black">The first important thing in making a dnd charakter is choosing a race. There are a lot of good options in this magical world and we wrote down the basic options.</p><br>

      <h5>Human</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">+1 to All Ability Scores, Extra Language</p><br>

      <h5>Dragonborn</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">+2 Strenght, +1 Charisma, Draconic Ancestry, Breath Weapon, Damage Resistance</p><br>

      <h5>Dwarf</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">+2 Constitution, Darkvision, Dwarven Resilience, Dwarven Combat Training, Stonecunning</p><br>

      <h5>Elf</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">+2 Dexterity, Darkvision, Keen Senses, Fey Ancestry, Trance</p><br>

	  <h5>Gnome</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">+2 Intelligence, Darkvision, Gnome Cunning</p><br>

	  <h5>Half-Elf</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">+2 Charisma, +2 to two other Ability Scores, Darkvision, Fey Ancestry, Skill Versatility</p><br>

	  <h5>Halfling</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">+2 Dexterity, Lucky, Brave, Halfling Nimbleness</p><br>

	  <h5>Half-Orc</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">+2 Strenght, +1 Constitution, Darkvision, Menasing, Relentless Endurance, Savage Attacks</p><br>

	  <h5>Tiefling</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">+2 Charisma, +1 Intelligence, Darkvision, Hellish Resistance, Infernal Legacy</p>
    </div>

	<div id="Classes" class="w3-container menu w3-padding-48 w3-card">
      <p class="w3-text-black">Choose your class wisely, and write your own backstory.</p><br>

      <h5>Barbarian</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">A fierce warrior who can enter a battle rage (Hit die:d12, Primary: Strenght, Saves: Strenght and Constitution)</p><br>

      <h5>Bard</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">An inspiring magician whose power echoes the music of creation (Hit die:d8, Primary: Charisma, Saves: Dexterity and Charisma)</p><br>

      <h5>Cleric</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">A priestly champion who wields divine magic in service of a higher power (Hit die:d8, Primary: Wisdom, Saves: Wisdom and Charisma)</p><br>

      <h5>Druid</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">A priest of the Old Faith, wielding the powers of nature and adopting animal forms (Hit die:d8, Primary: Wisdom, Saves: Intelligence and Wisdom)</p><br>

	  <h5>Fighter</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">A master of martial combat, skilled with a variety of weapons and armor (Hit die:d10, Primary: Strenght or Dexterity, Saves: Strenght and Constitution)</p><br>

	  <h5>Monk</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">A master of martial arts, harnessing the power of the body in pursuit of physical and spiritual perfection (Hit die:d8, Primary: Dexterity and Wisdom, Saves: Strenght and Dexterity)</p><br>

	  <h5>Palladin</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">A holy warior bound to a sacred oath (Hit die:d10, Primary: Strenght and Charisma, Saves: Wisdom and Charisma)</p><br>

	  <h5>Ranger</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">A warrior who combats threats on the edges of civilization (Hit die:d10, Primary: Dexterity and Wisdom, Saves: Strenght and Dexterity)</p><br>

	  <h5>Rogue</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">A scoundrel who uses stealth and trickery to overcome obstacles and enemies (Hit die:d8, Primary: Dexterity, Saves: Dexterity and Intelligence)</p><br>

	  <h5>Sorcerer</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">A spellcaster who draws on inherent magic from a gift or bloodline (Hit die:d6, Primary: Charisma, Saves: Constitution and Charisma)</p><br>

	  <h5>Warlock</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">A wielder of magic that is derived from a bargain with an extraplanar entity (Hit die:d8, Primary: Charisma, Saves: Wisdom and Charisma)</p><br>

	  <h5>Wizard</h5>
      <p class="w3-text-yellow">A scholarly magic-user capable of manipulating the structures of reality (Hit die:d6, Primary: Intelligence, Saves: Intelligence and Wisdom)</p>
    </div>

